{"addonId": "terminalAccess", "displayName": "Acesso ao terminal para NVDA", "URL": "https://github.com/PratikP1/Terminal-Access-for-NVDA/releases/download/v2.3.0/terminalAccess-2.3.0.nvda-addon", "description": "Oferece acessibilidade aprimorada ao terminal para o Windows Terminal e o PowerShell, permitindo que usu\u00e1rios de leitores de tela naveguem e interajam com efici\u00eancia com interfaces de linha de comando. Inspirado no TDSR (Terminal Data Structure Reader) e incorpora funcionalidades do TDSR e do Speakup. Recursos avan\u00e7ados inspirados em sugest\u00f5es e discuss\u00f5es da comunidade.", "sha256": "52c7351de86230ff5136e25aa05c757ae3fa734b24e25d1941e737eb6161205c", "addonVersionName": "2.3.0", "addonVersionNumber": {"major": 2, "minor": 3, "patch": 0}, "minNVDAVersion": {"major": 2025, "minor": 1, "patch": 0}, "lastTestedVersion": {"major": 2026, "minor": 1, "patch": 0}, "channel": "stable", "publisher": "Pratik Patel", "sourceURL": "https://github.com/PratikP1/Terminal-Access-for-NVDA/", "license": "GPL v3", "homepage": "https://github.com/PratikP1/Terminal-Access-for-NVDA", "changelog": "v2.3.0 collects everything since 2.0.3.\n\nNew: the buffer window. Press NVDA+Enter in a terminal to open the whole scrollback as a browsable snapshot: arrow through it, press H to move between the commands you ran and the errors they produced, follow the table of contents, read columnar output as real tables, and activate web links. NVDA+Shift+Enter opens a jump to line dialog that moves the review cursor to any line, found by its text. In the command layer, Shift+E shows only errors and Shift+C only the commands you ran.\n\nAlso new: any terminal NVDA recognizes is supported, not just those on a built-in list, so terminals the add-on used to ignore now work. Find reaches the scrollback on the legacy Windows console, where NVDA can only read the visible screen. And there is an optional word echo for terminals.\n\nFixed: braille follows the cursor again. Typing did not update the display until you panned away and back, and it never jumped back to the cursor. Key echo also no longer requires turning NVDA's own typing settings off; inside terminals it replaces them.\n\nSecurity: passwords are no longer spoken by key echo. Characters are masked and completed words are never spoken while the terminal marks input as protected.\n\nLaptop keyboard layout: NVDA+Enter is NVDA's activate-navigator-object command; Terminal Access takes it only inside terminals. Use the command layer's Enter, or reassign in Input Gestures, if you need NVDA's command there.\n\nRequires NVDA 2025.1 or later. Existing settings are preserved on upgrade.", "licenseURL": "https://www.gnu.org/licenses/gpl-3.0.html", "submissionTime": 1784532407000, "vtScanUrl": "https://www.virustotal.com/gui/file/52c7351de86230ff5136e25aa05c757ae3fa734b24e25d1941e737eb6161205c", "scanResults": {"virusTotal": [{"_id": "52c7351de86230ff5136e25aa05c757ae3fa734b24e25d1941e737eb6161205c", "_type": "file", "bundle_info": {"extensions": {"css": 1, "html": 1, "ini": 18, "md": 1, "mo": 17, "po": 17, "py": 31}, "file_types": {"HTML": 1, "unknown": 85}, "highest_datetime": "2026-07-20 07:19:34", "lowest_datetime": "2026-07-20 07:18:56", "num_children": 86, "type": "ZIP", "uncompressed_size": 2513887}, "contenthash": "e49609230ce90b38860a8f2f3e54bf9c", "filecondis": {"dhash": "0000000004070400", "raw_md5": "aac86119f1809494938d888d97fbaa71"}, "first_submission_date": 1784532411, "last_analysis_date": 1784532411, "last_analysis_results": {"ALYac": {"category": "undetected", "engine_name": "ALYac", "engine_update": "20260720", "engine_version": "2.0.0.10", "method": "blacklist", "result": null}, "APEX": {"category": "type-unsupported", "engine_name": "APEX", "engine_update": "20260719", "engine_version": "6.800", "method": "blacklist", "result": null}, "AVG": {"category": "undetected", "engine_name": "AVG", "engine_update": "20260720", "engine_version": "23.9.8494.0", "method": "blacklist